# 📂 Project Structure Rules - Feature-First Architecture

## Folder Structure Overview

```
src/
├── app/                    # Application Layer (routing, providers, layouts)
├── assets/                 # Static files (fonts, images, styles)
├── components/             # GLOBAL Shared Components
├── config/                 # Environment & Constants
├── features/               # ⚡ CORE BUSINESS LOGIC (Feature modules)
├── hooks/                  # Global custom hooks
├── lib/                    # Infrastructure (API client, Socket, utilities)
├── stores/                 # Global Zustand stores
├── types/                  # Global TypeScript definitions
└── widgets/                # 🧩 Large Composite UI Blocks (Header, Sidebar, CommandPalette)
```

## File Placement Rules by Directory

### `src/app/` - Application Layer
- `layouts/` - Layout components (MainLayout, AuthLayout)
- `providers/` - Context Providers (ThemeProvider, QueryClientProvider)
- `router.tsx` - Route definitions with Protected Routes

### `src/assets/` - Static Files
- `fonts/` - Custom font files
- `images/` - Images, logos, illustrations
- `styles/` - Global CSS/Tailwind styles

### `src/components/` - Shared Components
- `ui/` - shadcn/ui primitives ONLY (Button, Input, Card...)
- `common/` - App-specific shared (LoadingSpinner, ErrorBoundary, Logo)
- `icons/` - Custom SVG icon components
- `form/` - Form wrappers (React Hook Form + Zod integration)

### `src/features/` - Business Logic Modules
Each feature is an independent module with the following structure:
```
features/{feature-name}/
├── api/            # REST API calls for the feature
├── components/     # UI components used ONLY in this feature
├── hooks/          # Custom hooks for the feature
├── stores/         # Zustand slice for the feature
├── types/          # TypeScript interfaces for the feature
├── schemas/        # Zod validation schemas (optional)
└── index.ts        # Barrel export (public API)
```

### `src/widgets/` - Large Composite UI Blocks
Widgets are large UI blocks that combine multiple components/features together.
Unlike components (simple, reusable), widgets are **composite blocks with their own logic**.

```
widgets/{widget-name}/
├── components/     # Internal sub-components
├── hooks/          # Hooks specific to the widget
├── types/          # TypeScript interfaces
└── index.ts        # Barrel export
```

**Example widgets:**
- `header/` - App header with navigation, user menu, notifications
- `sidebar/` - Sidebar with menu items, collapse logic
- `command-palette/` - Command palette with search, shortcuts
- `battle-map/` - Composite tactical map (map + controls + overlays)

**When to create a widget instead of a component?**
- Combines 3+ sub-components together
- Has complex state/logic of its own
- Appears on multiple pages but does NOT belong to a single specific feature
- Too large to place in `components/common/`

### `src/config/` - Environment & Constants
- `env.ts` - Environment variables typed wrapper
- `constants.ts` - App-wide constants
- `routes.ts` - Route path constants

### `src/lib/` - Infrastructure
- `api-client.ts` - Axios instance with Bearer Token interceptor
- `socket-client.ts` - Socket.IO singleton instance
- `storage.ts` - Typed localStorage wrapper
- `utils.ts` - Helper functions (cn, formatters)

### `src/stores/` - Global State
- `use-auth-store.ts` - Authentication state
- `use-app-store.ts` - UI state (sidebar, theme)
- `use-socket-store.ts` - Socket connection status

### `src/types/` - Global TypeScript Definitions
- `api.ts` - API response/request types
- `common.ts` - Shared utility types
- `env.d.ts` - Environment type declarations

## Colocation Rules (Keep Related Files Together)

1. **Component used in only 1 feature** → Place in `features/{name}/components/`
2. **Component used in 2+ features** → Place in `src/components/common/`
3. **Large composite UI block, cross-feature** → Place in `src/widgets/{name}/`
4. **Hook used in only 1 feature** → Place in `features/{name}/hooks/`
5. **Hook used in multiple places** → Place in `src/hooks/`

## Dependency Rules (Import Direction)

```
app/ → widgets/ → features/ → components/ → lib/
                                           → stores/
                                           → hooks/
                                           → types/
                                           → config/
```

- `app/` can import from anywhere
- `widgets/` can import from features/, components/, lib/, stores/
- `features/` can import from components/, lib/, stores/, types/ — DO NOT import from another feature
- `components/` can only import from lib/, types/, config/
- `lib/` must not import from any other layer (except types/, config/)

## Import Rules

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT - Import from barrel file
import { ChatInput, MessageList } from '@/features/chat';
import { AppHeader } from '@/widgets/header';

// ❌ WRONG - Direct import into internal module
import { ChatInput } from '@/features/chat/components/chat-input';
import { NavMenu } from '@/widgets/header/components/nav-menu';
```
